# Nexus AI Workspace Frontend — environment guidance
#
# Application-specific examples are canonical:
#   - apps/web/.env.example
#   - apps/mobile/.env.example
#
# Client applications may only receive PUBLIC configuration.
# Never place secrets, private API keys, database credentials, JWT signing
# secrets, OAuth client secrets, or infrastructure tokens in Web or React Native
# environment files or public configuration sources.
#
# Values embedded in client bundles are visible to end users.
